U-factorization does, the algorithm should ",{"attributes":{},"tag":"code","children":["convert(AbstractMatrix,cache.A)"],"type":"node"},". The flag ",{"attributes":{},"tag":"code","children":["cache.isfresh"],"type":"node"}," states whether ",{"attributes":{},"tag":"code","children":["A"],"type":"node"}," has changed since the last ",{"attributes":{},"tag":"code","children":["solve"],"type":"node"},". Since we only need to factorize when ",{"attributes":{},"tag":"code","children":["A"],"type":"node"}," is new, the factorization part of the algorithm is done in a ",{"attributes":{},"tag":"code","children":["if cache.isfresh"],"type":"node"},". ",{"attributes":{},"tag":"code","children":["cache = set_cacheval(cache, fact)"],"type":"node"}," puts the new factorization into the cache so it's updated for future solves. Then ",{"attributes":{},"tag":"code","children":["y = ldiv!(cache.u, cache.cacheval, cache.b)"],"type":"node"}," performs the solve and a linear solution is returned via ",{"attributes":{},"tag":"code","children":["SciMLBase.build_linear_solution(alg,y,nothing,cache)"],"type":"node"},"."],"type":"node"}],"type":"node"}],"type":"node"}